</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table></para>
<para id="fs-id1169596275520">Plot the points, check that they line up, and draw the line.<newline/>
<media id="fs-id1169596310903" alt="The figure shows a straight line drawn through three points on the x y-coordinate plane. The x-axis of the plane runs from negative 7 to 7. The y-axis of the plane runs from negative 7 to 7. Dots mark off the three points which are labeled by their ordered pairs (negative 2, 6), (0, 0), and (1, negative 3). A straight line goes through all three points. The line has arrows on both ends pointing to the outside of the figure. The line is labeled with the equation y equals negative 3x.">
<image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="../../media/CNX_ElemAlg_Figure_04_02_011_img_new.jpg"/>
</media></para>
</solution>
</exercise>
</example>
<note id="fs-id1169596656657" class="try">
<exercise id="fs-id1169594157527">
<problem id="fs-id1169594159171">
