<para id="fs-id1169594156783">Plot the points, check that they line up, and draw the line.<newline/>
<media id="fs-id1169594189788" alt="The figure shows a straight line drawn through three points on the x y-coordinate plane. The x-axis of the plane runs from negative 7 to 7. The y-axis of the plane runs from negative 7 to 7. Dots mark off the three points which are labeled by their ordered pairs (0, 3), (2, 4), and (4, 5). A straight line goes through all three points. The line has arrows on both ends pointing to the outside of the figure. The line is labeled with the equation y equals (one half)x plus 3.">
