<para id="fs-id1169596516363">What if the equation has <m:math><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:math> but no <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math>? Let’s graph the equation <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>. This time the <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>- value is a constant, so in this equation, <m:math><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:math> does not depend on <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math>. Fill in 4 for all the <m:math><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:math>’s in <link target-id="fs-id1169594030456"/> and then choose any values for <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math>. We’ll use 0, 2, and 4 for the <emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>-coordinates.</para>
