<note id="fs-id1169596409604">
<title>Horizontal Line</title>
<para id="fs-id1169596409609">A <term>horizontal line</term> is the graph of an equation of the form <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>b</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>.</para>
<para id="fs-id1169596409625">The line passes through the <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>-axis at <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mi>b</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>.</para>
</note>
<para id="fs-id1171791531282"> </para>
<example id="fs-id1169596409650">
<exercise id="fs-id1169596409653">
<problem id="fs-id1169596409655">
<para id="fs-id1169596409657">Graph the equation <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>−1</m:mn><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1169596652708">
<title>Solution</title>
<para id="fs-id1169596652714">The equation <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>−1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> has only one variable, <m:math><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:math>. The value of <m:math><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:math> is constant. All the ordered pairs in <link target-id="fs-id1169596652759"/> have the same <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>-coordinate. The graph is a horizontal line passing through the <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>-axis at <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>−1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>, as shown in <link target-id="CNX_ElemAlg_Figure_04_02_037"/>.</para>
