<note id="fs-id1169594008580" class="try">
<exercise id="fs-id1169594008584">
<problem id="fs-id1169594008586">
<para id="fs-id1169594008588">Graph the equation <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>−4</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>.</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1169594008602">
<para id="fs-id1169594008604"><media id="fs-id1169594008605" alt="The figure shows a straight horizontal line drawn on the x y-coordinate plane. The x-axis of the plane runs from negative 12 to 12. The y-axis of the plane runs from negative 12 to 12. The straight line goes through the points (negative 4, negative 4), (0, negative 4), (4, negative 4), and all other points with second coordinate negative 4. The line has arrows on both ends pointing to the outside of the figure.">
