<section id="fs-id1169594154422" class="key-concepts">
<title>Key Concepts</title>
<list id="fs-id1169594154430" list-type="bulleted" bullet-style="bullet">
<item><emphasis effect="bold">Graph a Linear Equation by Plotting Points</emphasis>
<list id="fs-id1169594079036" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic" class="stepwise">
<item>Find three points whose coordinates are solutions to the equation. Organize them in a table.</item>
<item>Plot the points in a rectangular coordinate system. Check that the points line up. If they do not, carefully check your work!</item>
<item>Draw the line through the three points. Extend the line to fill the grid and put arrows on both ends of the line.</item>
</list></item>
</list>
</section>
<section id="fs-id1169594028663" class="section-exercises">
